tactful /ˈtæktfəl/

1. ADJ If you describe a person or what they say as tactful you approve of them because they are careful not to offend or upset another person. 有分寸的 [表赞许] 

例： He had been extremely tactful in dealing with the financial question. 他在处理这个财务问题时一直非常有分寸。 

2. tactfully ADV 有分寸地 

例： Alex tactfully refrained from further comment. 亚历克斯很有分寸地不多作评论。

